<ENAMEX TYPE="NORP">Brazilian</ENAMEX> officials say an oil tanker has crashed into a pier in a resort area , spilling <ENAMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">more than 86,000 liters</ENAMEX> of crude oil into the ocean .
The state - owned <ENAMEX TYPE="ORG">Petro Basque</ENAMEX> tanker hit the concrete pier in <ENAMEX TYPE="GPE">San Sebastian</ENAMEX> , a popular resort south of <ENAMEX TYPE="GPE">Sao Paulo</ENAMEX> .
Workers sealed the leaking hull and contained the spill , but authorities say the oil is still threatening local beaches .
<ENAMEX TYPE="DATE">Saturday</ENAMEX> 's incident was the <ENAMEX TYPE="ORDINAL">sixth</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="ORG">Petro Basque</ENAMEX> spill <ENAMEX TYPE="DATE">this year</ENAMEX> .
